column5: Was up there 2 weeks ago, fishing was wicked. Water level is down about a foot but the eye's are still where they should be. 31" is the biggest caught but had a really nice pike grab an eye being reeled in and lost him. Must have been 25lbs+

Was in an outpost just south of there a couple weeks ago, also. The water is down more like five feet from last year. By all means, it is wicked getting around until you find the rock you have never seen before. Fishing is fanastic.
